Cell.Text: A little history, first. After the Oblivion Crisis, a number of groups cropped up dedicated to wiping out the remnants of the Mythic Dawn. | One of these groups found Mehrunes' Razor, the artifact of Dagon. They split it into three fragments and pledged to keep them apart forever. | That was almost 150 years ago, and the pieces are still being kept by the descendants of that group. And they're right here, in Skyrim.

Node.Caption: DA07QuestGiveBranchTopic: Let's talk about this job you want done.

Cell.Text: [S] At least two of the owners, Ghunzul and Drascua, are dangerous marauders. And the third owner, Jorgen, I only know he lives in Morthal. | Here are my notes about them. I'll gladly pay you for getting the pieces any way you can. No questions asked.

Node.Caption: DA07QuestGiveTopic01: You want me to get those fragments?

Cell.Text: [S] S|Look at them. The legendary sharpness of a deadric weapon. Marvelous. | And here's your payment for the shards.

Node.Caption: DA07HaveBladeBranchTopic: I have the blade shards of Mehrunes' Razor.

Cell.Text: [S] S|Our master craftsman are nothing compared to the perfection of the Daedra. Look at how it shines. | Here's your gold, as promised.

Node.Caption: DA07HavePommelBranchTopic: Here's the pommel stone of Mehrunes' Razor.

Cell.Text: [S] S|Did you try the grip? Isn't it eerie how it seems to mold itself into your hand? | Here's your gold.

Node.Caption: DA07HaveHiltBranchTopic: The hilt of Mehrunes' Razor, as promised.

Cell.Text: Finally, all the pieces of Mehrunes' Razor are in my hands. It's time I let you in on something. | There's a fourth piece. That scabbard in the display case. Built to house the Razor. And there's more. | I know how to put all the pieces together. We just need to take them to Dagon's shrine and contact the Lord of Change directly.
We just need the shards of the blade and the hilt, now.
We just need the pommel and the shards of the blade, now.
We just need the hilt and the pommel, now.
There's only the shards of the blade left to collect. Exciting, isn't it?
There's only the pommel left to collect. Exciting, isn't it?
There's only the hilt left to collect. Exciting, isn't it?
Fine. I can't force you to help me, but the offer is open.

Node.Caption: DA07QuestGiveTopic02: Stop right there. I'm not interested.

Cell.Text: [S] S|And here you are. I hope you've found the museum to your liking.

Node.Caption: DA07PamphletBranchTopic: A courier gave me this pamphlet...

Cell.Text: [S] All at once! You're efficient. I like that. Here's your reward.

Node.Caption: DA07HaveAllPiecesBranchTopic: I have all the pieces of the Razor.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Ever since I was a boy, I felt this strange sense of destiny surrounding the Mythic Dawn cult, and now I know what it is. | Don't you see? Fate has led you to me and to the pieces. Dagon has to answer our call. We're so close. | I'll meet you at the shrine.

Node.Caption: DA07SilusRazor01: You think Dagon will repair the Razor?

Cell.Text: [S] G|You don't want to be part of history? Fine. I'll be at the shrine if you change your mind.

Node.Caption: DA07SilusRazor02: This sounds like a terrible idea...

Cell.Text: [S] G|Good. You're here. I'll place the pieces on the altar, and Dagon should speak to us.
G|I'll meet you at the shrine.
G|Let me put the pieces on the altar. We'll see if Mehrunes Dagon can still be reached.
G|Try putting your hands on the altar. Maybe Mehrunes Dagon will speak to you.

Cell.Text: [S] Wait. Wait. Don't kill me. There's another way. | I can take the pieces back to my museum. Seal them in a display case. | You get a generous amount of gold, I get to complete my collection, and nobody has to die.

Node.Caption: DA07SilusPleadForcegreetBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: [S] G|Fine. I'm not dying without a fight!
[S] G|Thank you. Here's your gold. I'll make a run for it back to Dawnstar.
